#: dashboard/build/index.js:66197
msgid "Why Do I Need to Install WDesignKit If I Already Have Nexter Blocks?"
msgstr ""

#: dashboard/build/index.js:66197
msgid "Using WDesignKit you will get access of extra Gutenberg Blocks, which is not part of Nexter Blocks. Those blocks built from Block Builder of WDesignKit and You can edit them from our Easy to Use Gutenberg Block Builder as well."
msgstr ""

#: dashboard/build/index.js:66198
msgid "Why Can’t These Blocks Be Part of Nexter Blocks?"
msgstr ""

#: dashboard/build/index.js:66198
msgid "We designed Nexter Blocks to focus on essential and core blocks that are required for most websites. WDesignKit, on the other hand, is a library with specialized creative blocks. You can download only those you want to use in WDesignKit."
msgstr ""

#: dashboard/build/index.js:66199
msgid "Will the Blocks Remain If I Remove WDesignKit?"
msgstr ""

#: dashboard/build/index.js:66199
msgid "No, the Blocks will be removed if you delete WDesignKit, as it is required for blocks used from WDesignKit."
msgstr ""

#: dashboard/build/index.js:66200
msgid "Will This Affect My Website Performance?"
msgstr ""

#: dashboard/build/index.js:66200
msgid "Not at all. Performance is our priority. WDesignKit will load assets of only blocks you downloaded and used on on that page. No extra assets will be loaded ever."
msgstr ""

